      "role": "user",
      "content": "i guess. but some historians argue a lot about the effectiveness of things like non-violence versus more militant approaches, or how much of the change was actually because of the government's own interests rather than just the activists. do you think there's any merit to those different viewpoints, or is it mostly just one way of looking at it?",
