      "content": "The idea that the government acted out of pure altruism is a myth; they only moved because the movement created an undeniable crisis that threatened their political survival. While non-violence was the moral compass that kept the movement united and earned national sympathy, militant tactics like sit-ins and freedom rides were absolutely necessary to break the system of segregation that polite protests couldn't touch. The historical record shows that without the pressure from both the disciplined marchers and the brave, sometimes disruptive activists, the federal government would have had no reason to intervene.",
